<br>
Archery - While not our 'primary occupation' the fact that rangers have gotten such HUGE advancements in terms of Archery they should perhaps bump warriors up a bit (who are the only other class that uses archery at any decent level). This is a huge nessessity in PvP servers since Rangers have become so ungodly overpowered with the AAs (Archery Mastery in particular tho endless quiver with 15 dmg arrows does pose a problem as well). Give us double damage with archery on still targets at 65 (Rangers get this at 50 or 55) and Endless Quiver (If rangers dont have to blow 100's of plat on archery neither should we). Nomatter how good we get with a bow a ranger will always have Trueshot (in combination with AM3, Endless Quiver, and other things) to outclass us with (just as warriors always have defensive/evasive to outclass other tanks with).<br>
<br>
Warlord's Steed - AA That would instantly summon a horse that is comparible to SK/Paladin horses but Tan in color (because us Warriors are poor suckers). We probably should have gotten this when Luclin came out with AA stuff but someone is biased against Warriors being semi-useful in PvP.<br>
<br>
Weapon Mastery (Type - Slashing, Blunt or Piercing) - Would increase damage dealt on melee damage of that type by 5%, 10% and 20% respectively. As well it would turn all critical hits with a weapon of that type to crippling blows regardless of health bar and any real 'crippling blows' will be turned into 'devistating blows' which would be double crippling blow damage, yeah this might mean a warrior with a good 2h weapon MIGHT score hits for 1k damage once and a while.<br>
<br>
Shields - it makes me sad I had to toss my shield at level 13. Perhaps adding WAR only shields with melee focus effect that double (or triple) melee damage output to compensate for the loss of damage from 2h weapons and the fact we dont have any over ratioed weapons like SK/Palys do with their 33/22 1hb's. If dual wield MTing is really dead in PoP then atleast have the decency to nail the coffin shut. As well it would be nice to be able to add 'procs' to shields which may or may not go off when you use bash.<br>
<br>
Disciplines - Hows about putting Evasive/Defensive on their own timers and all other discs on another timer. Include some discs which are focused towards utility discs or secondary tank duty (IE. One which nulls out Flurry/Rampage damage, ect...). Also hows about an AA which allows for shorter reuse times on disciplines? Otherwise those 60 minute disciplines will never see the light of day.<br>
<br>
Improved Combat Prowess - Allows our melee (Bash, Kick, Crippling Blows) to affect any monster under level 68. <p>Slowmotionz Unstopable<br>
Troll Warlord of Rallos Zek<br>
Ex-Badass of Malignant<br>
Warlord of Vindictive, Yo!<br>
