<br>
I think it'd be pretty neat to give warriors some of the combat-only, self-only, voice-only bard songs as a way of balancing the class a bit.  I'm not talking about charms or mezzes, but stuff like chant of battle, etc.  After all, we do alreay have a &quot;song&quot; effect- the o so uber warcry. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Would be... interesting to balance of course.<br>
<br>
Other fun/useful/overdue stuff:<br>
- channeling equal to hybrids, or bards, for click items.<br>
<br>
- give slam/bash/stun kick a hate &quot;proc&quot; effect, similar to what a low level paladin stun does.<br>
<br>
- how about some really outrageous warrior-only shields and 2handers?  Could put a &quot;/disc defensive&quot; type mitigation modifier on shields to promote their use, or make some insanely slow but hard hitting 2h weapons too... (/drool 150dmg/150dly weapon + rampage/furious heheh).<br>
<br>
- addition of &quot;block&quot; skill, perhaps as an expensive AA.<br>
<br>
- tracking!!!!<br>
<br>
Of course, all the above are &quot;wish list&quot; type things- would have to really think about how to balance them in-game, etc.  Some are obviously broken, others seem pretty reasonable...<br>
